uint8_t **  data 
)

Provides access to the internal byte array that stores the path segments.

Parameters
pathpointer to the path
[out]dataset to point to the path's internal byte array
Returns
the number of bytes in the data array

This function is to be used when serializing a path. The returned data array belongs to the path and must not be modified or freed.

Definition at line 466 of file bgpstream_utils_as_path.c.

int bgpstream_as_path_get_len ( bgpstream_as_path_t *  path)

Get the number of segments in the AS Path.

Parameters
pathpointer to the path to get the length of
Returns
the number of segments in the given path
Note
that this returns the number of BGPStream segments. This may not be the same as the number of segments in the original MRT message as BGPStream expands AS_SEQUENCE segments into a series of individual ASN segments.

bgpstream_as_path_iter_t *  iter 
)

Get the next segment from the given path.

Parameters
pathpointer to the AS path to get the segment from
iterpointer to an AS path iterator
Returns
borrowed pointer to the next segment, NULL if the path has no more segments
Note
the returned pointer is owned by the path. It MUST NOT be destroyed using bgpstream_as_path_seg_destroy. Also, it is only valid as long as the path is valid.
